bernini-r-mlx-swift
Copyright 2026 xocialize

Swift/MLX port of ByteDance Bernini-R (https://huggingface.co/ByteDance/Bernini-R-Diffusers,
Apache-2.0), whose renderer is stock Wan2.2-T2V-A14B (Alibaba Wan team, Apache-2.0).

Ported from the Python MLX implementation bernini-r-mlx (xocialize, Apache-2.0), which
reuses the Wan2.2 backbone from mlx-video (Blaizzy/mlx-video, MIT).

Wan-substrate Swift components (AutoencoderKLWan VAE, UMT5 encoder, attention/RoPE
patterns, weight loader) are adapted from longcat-avatar-mlx-swift (xocialize,
Apache-2.0), itself derived from the diffusers AutoencoderKLWan implementation
(HuggingFace, Apache-2.0).

This product includes software developed at:
- Apple (mlx, mlx-swift — MIT)
- HuggingFace (swift-transformers — Apache-2.0)
